 Career History



President & Chief Operating Officer

                                    2014 - Current                


City Office REIT, Inc.


                  City Office REIT, Inc. is a real estate investment trust, which intends to acquire, own and operate office properties primarily within the Southern and Western United States. It operates in one industry segment through commercial real estate. The company was founded on November 26, 2013 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.                




Limited Partner

                                    2011 - Current                


Second City General Partner II LP


                  Part of Gibralt Capital Corp, Second City General Partner II LP is a Canadian company located in Vancouver, BC. The firm provides investment advice.                




Managing Director

                                    2010 - Current                


Balfour Pacific Capital, Inc.


                  SCCP provides mezzanine debt and equity financing to middle-market companies throughout Canada and the Western and Midwestern US. The firm focuses on a wide range of industries including healthcare, industrial products and technology. They look for companies with exceptional management teams, leading and defensible market positions, large and well-defined market opportunities and strong financial disciplines. SCCP participates in management buy-outs and buy-ins, acquisitions financings, shareholder successions, restructurings, recapitalizations, expansion capital financings and bridge financings. Investments are typically made in the form of equity or equity-like instruments, mezzanine loans, bridge loans or a combination of these.                




President

                                    2008 - 2012                


Bosa Properties, Inc.


                  Bosa Properties Inc. provides construction services. The firm primarily engages in housing projects, new homes and commercial projects. The company was founded by Robert Bosa and is headquartered in Burnaby, Canada.                




Vice President

                                    2000 - Prior                


Ken Fowler Enterprises Ltd.


                  Ken Fowler Enterprises (KFE) core investment activities are focused on real estate development, restaurant companies/hospitality and niche specialty retailers. They look for companies with experienced management teams that are operating in industries with strong long-term potential. Companies should have or have the potential to have diversified suppliers and customers. They should also have or have the potential to have a significant market share of its sector or industry as a whole.                





